HOUSE JOINT RESOLUTION 806
By Powers
A RESOLUTION to recognize E.E. Hill & Son Insurance on the
occasion of its 100th anniversary.
WHEREAS, it is fitting that the members of this General Assembly should recognize
those historic Tennessee businesses that have a long-standing commitment to providing
exceptional service to their customers; and
WHEREAS, E.E. Hill & Son Insurance celebrated its 100th anniversary in 2025, a
commendable milestone for this family-owned and -operated business; and
WHEREAS, the company founder and namesake, Elbert Ellison Hill, or E.E. Hill, initially
owned an automobile dealership in downtown La Follette and deemed it worthwhile to sell
insurance policies to those purchasing his cars; and
WHEREAS, in 1938, E.E. Hill's son, Lansden "Lan" Hill, Sr., joined the insurance
agency; E.E. Hill retired in the mid-1960s, and Lan Hill brough his brother-in-law, David
Reynolds, into the business. Upon graduating from the University of Tennessee in 1974,
Lansden Hill, Lan Hill's son, joined the firm; and
WHEREAS, Lansden Hill, the grandson of E.E. Hill, has served at the agency for fifty-
one years; his father served the agency for thirty years and his grandfather for forty. Three
generations of Hill men grew the insurance agency from an office on the second floor of
Peoples National Bank to a nearby building and then to its current location at 701 West Central
Avenue; and
WHEREAS, E.E. Hill & Son Insurance continues to enjoy the leadership of the third
generation of the Hill family; much like his predecessors, Lansden Hill is committed to the
wellbeing of his employees, exceptional customer service, and the communities his agency so
ably serves; and
HJR0806
011568
- 1 -

WHEREAS, notable employees over the years include Elsie Kibler; Rissa Ward; Lola
Heatherly; and Cathy Owens and David Rutherford, who have been with the agency since the
late 1970s; and
WHEREAS, for a century, E.E. Hill & Son has been providing exceptional customer
service to the good people of La Follette and Campbell County, and it is fitting that the business
be recognized on this special occasion; now, therefore,
BE IT RESOLVED BY THE HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES OF THE ONE HUNDRED
FOURTEENTH GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF THE STATE OF TENNESSEE, THE SENATE
CONCURRING, that we congratulate E.E. Hill & Son Insurance on 100 years of operation,
wishing the iconic Tennessee business much continued success in the future.
BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED, that an appropriate copy of this resolution be prepared
for presentation with this final clause omitted from such copy and upon proper request made to
the appropriate clerk, the language appearing immediately following the State seal appear
without House or Senate designation.
